                            </h2>
        
        
        
            </div>

    
        
        
    
        
    <p>The African Cassava Whitefly Project is searching for answers to significantly reduce the cassava-whitefly abundance in the cassava-growing regions of East and Central Africa. Outbreaks of the African cassava whitefly are responsible for serious crop losses in nine East and Central African countries resulting in hunger, recurrent famines and annual losses of more than USD1.25 billion.</p>

    
    
        
<p class="readmore">
